09/07/2003
ANKARA, Turkey -- Two soldiers died and another one was injured when a dozen suspected Kurdish rebels opened fire Tuesday (8 July) on a governor's convoy in the southeastern part of the country.
Ali Cafer Akyuz, the governor of the Tunceli province, was not injured.
An estimated 5,000 troops combed the area later, using air support.
President Ahmet Necdet Sezer condemned the attack and reaffirmed the government's determination to fight all threats to national unity.
(AP, Reuters, AFP, Anadolu Agency, NTV, TRT 2 - 08/07/03)
